&nbsp;

<a title="How long do sails last"><strong>How long do sails last?</strong></a>
<p class="p1">Day sails generally run 3-5 hours.Â  Voyages vary from 3-5 days.</p>

&nbsp;

<a title="What will my jobs on the boat will be my responsibility?"><strong>What will my jobs on the boat will be my responsibility?</strong></a>
<p class="p1">Everything!Â  Setting and taking in sail, furling (folding and putting away sail), tending docklines, doing deck washes, cooking, cleaning (we all contribute), navigating, helming, working in the rig, sanding painting, putting protective pine tar on stays...Â  Any job on the boat is available to you, but above all, your task is to be a good shipmate and make anyone who comes aboard feel welcome and included.</p>

&nbsp;

<a title="Iâ€™m scared of heights."><strong>Iâ€™m scared of heights. Do I have to climb aloft?</strong></a>
<p class="p1">No.Â  Everything we do aloft in the rig is â€œchallenge by choice.â€Â  That option applies equally to volunteers and students.Â  (If you want to try, though, weâ€™re always ready to encourage you and help you do so safely.)</p>

