If you are interested in becoming a member of our Youth Crew, recruit a parent or guardian to bring you to an <a title="Crew Training Schedule" href="http://198.1.99.216/volunteer/crew-training-schedule/">orientation meeting</a>. Once weâ€™ve introduced LAMIâ€™s programs to you and you have submitted your <a title="Forms &amp; Training Materials" href="http://198.1.99.216/volunteer/forms-training-materials/">forms</a>, you are welcome to sail with us. Youâ€™ll be taught by your peers (under the supervision of adult crew leaders), and eventually, youâ€™ll teach others â€“ including students your age in our TopSail Youth program, as they voyage during the summer. LAMIâ€™s Youth Crew generally takes over a boat the first Saturday of the month.Â  Check our <a title="Crew Training Schedule" href="http://198.1.99.216/volunteer/crew-training-schedule/">online calendar</a>Â to confirm, then email <a href="mailto:youthcrew@lamitopsail.org">youthcrew@lamitopsail.org</a> or call Big Ben in the office at (310) 833-6055 to sign up and sail!";s:10:"post_title";s:18:"Youth Crew Program";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:18:"youth-crew-program";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-11-26 03:06:27";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-11-26 03:06:27";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:3:"629";s:4:"guid";s:32:"http://198.1.99.216/?page_id=542";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"page";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:37;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"562";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"2";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-11-01 23:03:19";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-11-01 23:03:19";s:12:"post_content";s:1525:"<a href="/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/garfield_011.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-736" style="float: left; padding-right: 10px;" src="/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/garfield_011-300x199.jpg" alt="Navigation Lesson" width="300" height="199" /></a>We recently applied for a grant through Harbor Community Benefit Foundation's Harbor Schools: S.T.E.A.M. Initiative. Â Our TopSail S.T.E.M. Program builds on our signature TopSail Youth Program and leverages the S.T.E.M. framework inherent to our program. Â We're focusing on the "M" in S.T.E.M. (Mathematics) and working exclusively with Wilmington Middle School in order to expand our S.T.E.M. activities with the school's Science / Robotics program and College Core Curriculum program (CCC). Â We plan to serve approximately 240 students with this pilot program with a combination of in-classroom and at-sea learning activities. Â We will be using the Navigation component of our TopSail program to enhance students' interest in mathematics. Â Our Navigation curriculum is designed to teach students how to identify the symbols and data on a nautical chart. Â In this process they will be introduced to a nautical chart, its geometry Â and many of its symbols, then use that information to determine a course and relay it to a helmsman so that course can be steered. Â All of this work takes place in real-world scenarios aboard our tall ships. Â Each program participant will receive an interactive Student Logbook to aid their learning and track their progress.";s:10:"post_title";s:24:"TopSail S.T.E.M. Program";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:25:"topsail-s-t-e-a-m-program";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-01-28 16:13:09";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-01-28 16:13:09";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:3:"629";s:4:"guid";s:32:"http://198.1.99.216/?page_id=562";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"page";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:38;O:8:"